<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 3:20AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Oldham
and northwestern Deaf Smith Counties through 345 AM CDT...
At 320 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southwest of Adrian, or 22 miles west of Vega, moving northeast
at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Vega, Adrian and Simms.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
